  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Hi,\r\nI'm trying to give tasks parameters some nice names, but it seems that there is a conflict and only lowercase param names can be used.\r\n\r\nSome example I encountered with hardhat v2.6.8\r\n``` \r\nnpx harhdhat fake --long-name-param \"foo\"\r\n```\r\ngives the error \r\n```Error HH208: Invalid param name long-name-param in task fake. Param names must be camelCase.```\r\n\r\nwhile this\r\n``` \r\nnpx harhdhat fake --longNameParam \"foo\"\r\n```\r\ngives the error \r\n```Error HH310: Invalid param --longNameParam. Command line params must be lowercase.```\r\n\r\nIs there a way to use such param name format? \r\n\r\n",
