    "body": "You need to define your task in camelCase, but you use it in the terminal as kebab-case:\r\n\r\n```js\r\ntask(\"fake\")\r\n  .addParam(\"longNameParam\")\r\n  .setAction(async (taskArgs, hre) => {\r\n    // do stuff\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nnpx hardhat fake --long-name-param value\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe reason for this is that you can then use the param as `taskArgs.longNameParam` instead of `taskArgs[\"long-name-param\"]`, but it's understandably confusing at first.\r\n\r\nI hope this helps. I you have more questions, please use [our Discord server](https://hardhat.org/discord) or [GitHub's discussions](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/discussions).",
